## 🚀 Step-by-Step Process

### Task 2: [How to Interact with a Shell]
1. ls, cd, grep... basic stuff

### Task 3: [Types of Linux Shells]
1. zshell - switch by just typing zsh + ENTER
2. Change default shell chsh -s /usr/bin/...      - ... = zsh, bash - shell name
3. history		- displays command history

Types:
	Bourne Again SHell		- BASH
	Z Shell				- ZSh
	Friendly Interactive SHell	- FISH
---

### Task 4: [Shell Scripting and Components]
- How to write a shell script
Start with shebang:		#!/bin/bash
echo				echo "sth"
read				read var
echo read			echo "$var"
loop				for i in {1...10}
				do
				...
				done
if,elif,else			if [ cond ]; then
					...
				elif [ cond ]; then
					...
				else
					...
				fi

### Task 5: [The Locker Script]
- wrote a little script that applies the control structures learned above


## 💡 Key Takeaways

- blends well with previous coding experience. Cool that one can do this from the terminal

